				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Thinking about putting Guard II or Guard III on my epic...<a name="59819"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 31 04 5:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I read a post a couple of weeks ago about this.
<br />

<br />
If memory serves, the first number is a game mechanics number that has to do with level scaling (or something like that).  The second number is the percentage of incoming damage (per hit) that will be absorbed by the guard.  The third number is the maximum damage the guard will absorb before it drops (unless the 5 minute duration wears off first).
<br />

<br />
IMO, unless you are MT'ing a LOT, I wouldn't go with any of the GUARD augs.  You will get better service in the long run with pure damage augs and/or lifetap augs.  My preference is straight DD-type damage augs.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
