				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Thinking about putting Guard II or Guard III on my epic...<a name="59855"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 31 04 11:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I haven't had any desire to test, but I believe the first number represents the maximum number of hits it will absorb before fading, the second number is how much it will take off the damage, and the third the maximum amount of damage the effect will absorb before fading. 
<br />

<br />
For instance, for the sake of argument, Guard3 will either absorb 200 damage off one hit of 4000 (meaning you take 3800 damage), or two hits of 2000 each (meaning you take 1900 damage each). 
<br />

<br />
Due to the limited amount of damage they absorb they seem pretty 'eh' as far as effectiveness. But I don't find that rune procs or lifetaps do much either. I believe even the 75pt lifetap, in the hands of a class which can maximize healing and spell critial AAs (a ranger, beastlord, or paladin) only provides at best a +5 or +8hp/tick regen over a long period of time. That is nothing compared to what you see in PoP and beyond.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
